fields.name: Fungal infection
fields.description:
A fungal infection, also called mycosis, is a skin disease caused by a fungus.

There are millions of species of fungi. They live in the dirt, on plants, on household surfaces, and on your skin. Sometimes, they can lead to skin problems like rashes or bumps.
There 3 common types of fungal infections name:
1. Athletes foot -  is commonly associated with sports and athletes because the fungus grows perfectly in warm, moist environments.
2. Yeast infection - is a common fungal infection of the genitals mostly called vaginal yeast infection.. It causes inflammation, irritation, itching, and vaginal discharge. It can affect people of all genders.
3. Jock Itch - The infection is also known as tinea cruris. Tinea loves warm, moist areas like your genitals, inner thighs, and buttocks. Infections happen more often in the summer or in warm, wet climates.
fields.treatments: Fungal infections can be cured with antifungal medication, which kills fungus in and on your body.

Use salicylic acid as it helps to correct the abnormal shedding of cells

fields.name: Paralysis (brain hemorrhage)
fields.description:
Paralysis is the loss of voluntary muscle function in one or more parts of the body as a result of damage to the nervous system.
 It happens when something goes wrong with the way messages pass between your brain and muscles.
NB: In many cases paralysis is not curable & also the effects depend on the type of paralysis.
fields.treatments: Surgery, Physical therapy, Mobileaids such as wheelchairs and braces, Medication such as Brotox or muscle relaxers.

fields.name: Alcoholic hepatitis
fields.description:
Alcoholic hepatitis is inflammation of the liver caused by drinking alcohol.
It is most likely to occur in people who drink heavily over many years. However, the relationship between drinking and alcoholic hepatitis is complex. Not all heavy drinkers develop alcoholic hepatitis, and the disease can occur in people who drink only moderately.
fields.treatments: Stop alcohol consumption and see a doctor

fields.name: Allergy
fields.description: An allergy is where your body reacts to something that's normally harmless like pollen, dust or animal fur. The symptoms can be mild, but for some people they can be very serious.
fields.treatments: Try to avoid the thing you're allergic to, mergency medicines called adrenaline auto-injectors for severe allergic reactions

fields.name: Arthritis
fields.description: Arthritis is the swelling and tenderness of one or more joints. The main symptoms of arthritis are joint pain and stiffness, which typically worsen with age.
fields.treatments: medicines, such as painkillers, anti-inflammatory medicines or medicines to slow down the disease
